article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 48, SE Louisiana 45
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Cory Long kicked a 23-yard field goal with 7 seconds left, completing a 24-point rally for Stephen F. Austin in a 48-45 victory over Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday night. Jeremy Moses threw for four touchdowns and 319 yards for the Lumberjacks (2-3, 1-0 Southland), who trailed 45-21 midway through the third quarter before outscoring the Lions 27-0 the rest of the way. Moses went 24-of-50 with one interception and spread the ball to 10 different receivers, including Dominiq Edison, who caught six passes for 173 yards and two touchdowns. Brian Babin completed 30-of-42 passes for 272 yards, four touchdowns and one interception for Southeastern Louisiana (3-3, 0-1). Chris Wilson hauled in five passes for 121 yards and two touchdowns for the Lions, and Sim Yarborough also caught two TDs.
